[[File:Jar-Kai_dueling_sabers.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A pair of sabers owned by Ace Azzameen]]
The '''Jar'Kai dueling sabers''' were a set of weapons developed by the [[Yovshin Swordsmen]] on [[Atrisia/Legends|Atrisia]]. Named after a [[Jar'Kai (city)|city]] on Atrisia, the weapons were designed to be dual-wielded, leading to the creation of the [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber combat]] style [[Jar'Kai/Legends|Jar'Kai]].<ref name="DF Saga">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050526a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 4: Of the Crudest Matter}}</ref>

[[Antan Azzameen]] possessed a set of Jar'Kai dueling sabers, which was rumored to have been the result of a duel that he won against a [[Prince/Legends|prince]]. He later gave his nephew, [[Ace Azzameen/Legends|Ace Azzameen]], his set as thanks for rescuing him from [[Viraxo Industries (platform)|Viraxo Industries]]. Ace then put the weapons on display in his quarters as part of his collection, keeping them even after Antan betrayed him and [[Azzameen family|his family]].<ref name="XWA">''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Alliance]]''</ref>

